<Base
  title="Carrados and Zero Information Casualty | Charli-Jo Tyrer"
  description="Carrados is Charli-Jo Tyrer's accessibility and agent-first design work on generative accessibility, non-visual interfaces and Zero Information Casualty."
>
  <h1>Carrados</h1>
  <p class="site-intro">Carrados is the accessibility and agent-first design work of Charli-Jo Tyrer.</p>

  <section aria-labelledby="what-is-carrados">
    <h2 id="what-is-carrados">What Carrados is</h2>
    <p>Carrados begins from the idea that digital systems should not merely comply with accessibility rules. They should actively reduce informational suffering.</p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="the-problem">
    <h2 id="the-problem">The problem</h2>
    <p>Information is lost when systems assume sight, a particular interface, a particular tool or a particular way of reading. That loss is not neutral: someone pays for it in time, effort, exclusion or uncertainty.</p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="agent-first-design">
    <h2 id="agent-first-design">Agent-first design</h2>
    <p>Carrados explores AI for blind and disabled people, generative accessibility, non-visual interfaces, accessible AI assistants and information that remains usable across people, tools and formats.</p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="zic">
    <h2 id="zic">Zero Information Casualty</h2>
    <p>Zero Information Casualty is a design principle and technical standard for preserving information across human and machine access.</p>
    <p>A ZIC system should not lose essential meaning when content moves between visual and non-visual interfaces, HTML and Markdown, humans and agents, websites and assistive technology.</p>
    <p>ZIC asks a simple question: What information was lost, and who paid the price?</p>
    <p>Charli.info follows the ZIC 1.5 baseline established in this repository.</p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="current-work">
    <h2 id="current-work">Current work</h2>
    <p>Carrados is a home for ongoing work on accessible AI, agent-first websites and digital systems that preserve meaning across changing conditions.</p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="about-charli-jo">
    <h2 id="about-charli-jo">About Charli-Jo Tyrer</h2>
    <p>Charli-Jo Tyrer is a blind writer, conceptual artist and accessibility thinker working with generative AI, design fiction and agent-first digital systems.</p>
  </section>

  <p><a href="/">Back to Charli.info</a></p>
</Base>
